To calculate the Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio, we use the formula:

\[
\text{Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio} = \frac{\text{Net Credit Sales}}{\text{Average Accounts Receivable}}
\]

Step 1: Determine Net Credit Sales  
From the Income Statement, Total Revenue = 28,572,608.70  
Assuming all sales are credit sales (usually total revenue is used for this ratio unless specified), so Net Credit Sales = 28,572,608.70

Step 2: Calculate Average Accounts Receivable  
Initial Accounts Receivable (at 2023-12-31) = 0.00  
Ending Accounts Receivable (at 2024-02-05) = 14,921,566.06  

Average Accounts Receivable = (0.00 + 14,921,566.06) / 2 = 7,460,783.03

Step 3: Calculate the Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio

\[
= \frac{28,572,608.70}{7,460,783.03} \approx 3.83
\]

So, the Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio is approximately 3.83.
